          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπι - τρέπω</span></b> , aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπέτρεψα</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπέτραπον</span>, imp. 2 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιτράφεθ̓</span>, mid. aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπετραπόμην</span>, pass. perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιτέτραμμαι</span>, 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιτετράφαται</span>: act., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">turn</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">give
            over to, commit, intrust</span>, pass., <i><span class="en">Il.
            2.25</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.750</span></i>; of ‘leaving’
          the victory to another, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.473</span></i>;
          intr., ‘give up,’ ‘give in to,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γήραϊ</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 10.79</span></i>; mid. (met.), <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be
            inclined</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμός</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.12</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
